gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 129, Timberwolves 106
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder defeated the Timberwolves, 129-106. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander recorded a team-high 34 points, along with six rebounds and nine assists for the Thunder, while Jalen Williams (21 points) and Chet Holmgren (20 points) added a combined 41 points in the victory. Anthony Edwards tallied 25 points, seven rebounds and six assists for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The Thunder improve to 19-9 on the season, while the Timberwolves fall to 22-7.
